            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>I worry about the worst case scenario, in which people made hopeful by improved access to healthcare are forced to go uninsured, dependent on the local emergency room for medical treatment.</p>
<p>If the Trump administration can provide those benefits better, great. But enough with the vague hyperbole; tell me how. And, in the meantime, let’s hope for once that Trump creates something as “great” as he says it is.</p>
<p><em>Jake Parker is a Trinity sophomore. His column, "thinking too much, feeling too little," runs on alternate Wednesdays.</em></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: " times="" new="" roman";="" font-style:="" italic;="" vertical-align:="" baseline;="" white-space:="" pre-wrap;"=""></span></p>

